  "wlStep1Title": "Why bother?",
  "wlStep1Body": "Your staff's phones and your own sit in the shop all day. The device works them out by itself after about 6 hours and stops counting them as customers - but you can add them right now instead of waiting.",
  "wlStep2Title": "Hold the button for 3 seconds",
  "wlStep2Body": "The LED starts blinking amber quickly. That means the device is waiting - you have 30 seconds.",
  "wlStep3Title": "Hold the phone right next to the device",
  "wlStep3Body": "Really close - the device only accepts a very strong signal, so it can't grab a customer standing nearby by mistake. Done: that phone no longer counts as a visitor.",
  "wlStep4Title": "Check it worked",
  "wlStep4Body": "The device screen shows \"Background devices\" and how many there are. We never see which phones they are, only how many.",
  "exStep1Title": "Two different things",
  "exStep1Body": "\"Report\" is a tidy picture with the summary - for sending to a partner or your boss. \"Export\" is an Excel file with all the numbers - for doing your own maths.",
  "exStep2Title": "Pick the period",
  "exStep2Body": "Both ask which period: today, week or month. We don't guess for you.",
  "exStep3Title": "You choose where it goes",
  "exStep3Body": "Your phone's ordinary share sheet opens - mail, WhatsApp, whatever. We send nothing anywhere; the file goes where you point it.",
  "fwStep1Title": "Day 1 - pairing",
  "fwStep1Body": "The device starts counting the moment it has power. Your phone is only there to read the results - it doesn't need to be nearby.",
  "fwStep2Title": "Days 2-3 - mark your own",
  "fwStep2Body": "Add your staff's phones to the background list so they don't inflate the numbers. The device would get there by itself, but by hand is quicker.",
  "fwStep3Title": "From day 3 - the first insights",
  "fwStep3Body": "Insights and comparisons (\"today vs a typical Tuesday\") need a few days of history. Before that there's nothing to compare against, so the panel doesn't show them.",
  "fwStep4Title": "Monday - your summary",
  "fwStep4Body": "On Monday at 9:00 you get a notification with the week's summary. That's when you first see the full weekly pattern.",
  "tutorialDemoTitle": "Show it with example data?",
  "tutorialDemoBody": "You have no data yet, so the tutorial would be pointing at zeros. We can turn on demo mode with sample numbers, so you see exactly what the tutorial describes. You can turn it off any time in Settings.",
